comment0.text=\n\ A\ graphical\ component\ for\ displaying\ the\ contents\n\ of\ a\ binary\ tree.\ The\ following\ methods\ are\ designed\ \n\ for\ interacting\ with\ the\ display\:\n\ \ \ \ \ \ Default\ constructor\ TreeDisplay()\n\ \ \ \ \ \ displayTree(TreeNode\ someTree)\n\ \ \ \ \ \ visit(TreeNode\ someNode)\n\ The\ displayTree\ method\ creates\ the\ initial\ display\ of\n\ the\ tree.\ \ It\ clears\ the\ component\ and\ paints\ the\ tree\n\ The\ visit\ method\ changes\ the\ background\ color\ of\ the\n\ node\ defined\ in\ the\ parameter\n\ sample\ Useage\:\n\ TreeDisplay\ display\ \=\ new\ TreeDisplay();\n\ display.displayTree(someTree);\n\ display.visit(someNode);\n\ \n\ @author\ DaveF\n\ @author\ RichardP\n\ @version\ 11/4/2025\n\n
